The trial for Russell Henderson, accused in the beating death of Matthew Shepard, has been postponed to April 6 due to a scheduling conflict.
Henderson and Aaron McKinney face murder charges and the death penalty if convicted.
The attack on Shepard, motivated by his sexual orientation, sparked outrage.
Judy Shepard, Matthew's mother, advocated for hate-crime laws to prevent future violence.
Jury selection began amidst emotional pleas for justice.
The case, a focal point for gay rights activists, highlights the need for stronger bias crime legislation.
The trial's impact extends beyond the courtroom, shaping public perception and legal discourse.
